commit.message: Restore portchecker to yougetsignal
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/Novik/ruTorrent into develop

Add more tracker labels

For 1337x, torrentleech and iptorrents.

Drop support for RPC & optimize for httprpc

We can no longer support RPC for stability reasons. The web interface may start to fail at just 150 torrents.

The newer httprpc alternative is now a lot more stable and polished. By dropping support for rpc, we can bring the web interface update settings into this decade.

It's required to reduce the request time out, to ensure we do not overload  web servers. We can also run a lower update interval, due to threaded web interface updates in the browser.

This does not impact critical requests with no time out. If the request can potentially take longer than 10s, we should not be using a timeout for it.
Update other-errors.yml
Update javascript-errors.yml
Update Turkish translations

Update el.js

Update for Views panel

trafic: Fix resize when plot undefined

Additionally, loading the `trafic` plugin failed
when `tdetails` was collapsed, since the flot plot
does not allow width and height being 0.

Fixes: #2593

fix DE translations for alternating list background

the current translation means "alternative background" as opposed to the likely intended "alternating background". in german, the latter would be "Alternierender Listenhintergrund", but that is clunky phrasing. the change in this commit translates to "alternating line backgrounds" and is verbiage common to e.g. Excel.

Add internal hybrid creation of torrents

This commit adds a feature to create hybrid torrents using the internal method. It allows the external program to continue to be used for regular torrents. The benefit is added compatibility and optimization. This feature will be enabled by default.
